WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.791
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.292 --> 00:11.782
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWS.org.

00:14.345 --> 00:17.530
Today's message comes from senior pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.832 --> 00:23.720
This morning, I'm going to tackle a really, really sensitive and difficult topic.

00:23.740 --> 00:26.464
And I'm going to take a little time to do it just to let you know that.

00:27.125 --> 00:28.567
And if you have to leave, that's OK.

00:28.587 --> 00:30.610
But I'm on preach till I'm done this morning.

00:31.074 --> 00:42.850
Last Monday night, one of the few bright spots in the Dallas Cowboys loss on Monday night football was a blocked punt.

00:43.511 --> 00:44.592
The punt was blocked.

00:45.313 --> 00:51.762
It bounced into the end zone and defensive end, Marshawn Neland fell on it.

00:52.482 --> 01:00.531
He scored a touchdown for the Cowboys, and it was his first ever NFL touchdown that second year player had experienced.

01:00.551 --> 01:03.214
There was jubilation on the Cowboys' sideline.

01:03.234 --> 01:07.278
There was a celebration of what had happened in the football game.

01:08.039 --> 01:12.384
But 48 hours later, something went terribly wrong.

01:13.725 --> 01:21.874
Marshall and Neland was involved in a chase with DPS troopers and with the Frisco Police Department.

01:22.498 --> 01:32.129
Eventually, they lost sight of him, and so they broke off the chase, and then his vehicle was found, wrecked and abandoned on the side of the road, but it was empty.

01:32.989 --> 01:42.800
A search ensued, and later, 24-year-old Marshawn Neland was found dead of a self-inflicted gunshot wound.

01:44.142 --> 01:51.730
I planned these sermons back in September, and yet it seems that the news

01:51.842 --> 01:57.269
the headlines gave me fodder for simply introducing the topic.

01:58.331 --> 02:00.714
Suicide has touched many of us.

02:01.314 --> 02:10.166
As a matter of fact, most of us, our church, our family, our community, we have all been affected by suicide.

02:11.067 --> 02:19.218
As a pastor, I will tell you, there is nothing that is more painful than trying to help a family.

02:19.746 --> 02:26.456
who is navigating the anger, the grief, the hurt, and the shock of a loved one who commits suicide.

02:27.717 --> 02:38.713
Equally, there's nothing more bewildering, more frustrating, more confusing than being a pastor and trying to help someone who's having suicidal thoughts.

02:39.554 --> 02:47.826
I am under no illusion that I have all the answers this morning, but I do believe God's Word has answers for us.

02:48.130 --> 02:49.812
And that's what we're going to dig in on.

02:50.373 --> 02:57.782
But before I dig into the text, before we talk about the principles this morning, I want to say something to those of you who are watching this.

02:58.783 --> 03:07.354
I realize that things that are on the internet take on a life of their own and maybe five years from now, somebody could do a search and find this on the internet.

03:07.775 --> 03:13.522
And what I want to say to you is this, that if you're having thoughts of self-harm right now,

03:14.114 --> 03:17.519
I want you to stop watching me, and I want you to dial 988.

03:17.539 --> 03:29.435
988 is the National Suicide Crisis Hotline, and there's someone there who will talk to you right now about your issues.

03:30.577 --> 03:35.604
Suicide is at its highest level in 30 years.

03:35.624 --> 03:41.111
According to the Foundation for Suicide Prevention, it is the 10th most common cause of death in America.

03:41.872 --> 03:43.154
But worse than that,

03:43.874 --> 03:49.242
In 2023, there were 50,000 Americans who died by suicide.

03:49.783 --> 03:51.566
That's one death every 11 minutes.

03:52.147 --> 04:07.130
It is the second leading cause of death in the demographic between ages 10 and 34, nearly 1.7 million Americans attempted to commit suicide last year.

04:07.892 --> 04:08.973
But I want you to understand this.

04:09.093 --> 04:12.018
Behind every statistic, there is a soul

04:12.386 --> 04:20.073
created in the image of God, whom is desperately loved by the Lord Jesus Christ.

04:21.715 --> 04:27.480
And so this morning I want us to talk about this horrible, horrible epidemic of suicide.

04:28.441 --> 04:36.008
Drugs and alcohol exponentially multiply the damage and the tendencies towards suicide.

04:36.649 --> 04:39.452
Now the word suicide doesn't occur in scripture.

04:40.012 --> 04:41.874
It's not there.

04:42.530 --> 04:43.731
The concept does.

04:45.713 --> 04:52.860
The reality is that Jesus gives us a very clear line that he's drawn in John chapter 10, verse 10.

04:53.200 --> 04:54.782
And we're going to talk about that this morning.

04:55.422 --> 04:57.324
Look at verse 10 of John chapter 10.

04:58.425 --> 05:02.509
The thief comes, and by thief, he's referring to the enemy or Satan.

05:03.229 --> 05:08.995
The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy.

05:09.015 --> 05:12.338
I have come, Jesus says,

05:13.026 --> 05:17.152
so that they would have life and have it abundantly.

05:18.934 --> 05:24.542
The purpose and plan of Jesus is life and abundant life.

05:24.702 --> 05:25.943
It is eternal life.

05:26.564 --> 05:30.389
The word life is the word zoe in the language of the New Testament.

05:30.670 --> 05:32.472
It means more than just to exist.

05:32.933 --> 05:36.478
It is the fullness of a relationship with God.

05:37.219 --> 05:42.706
Jesus gives us the opportunity to participate in the life of God Himself.

05:43.202 --> 05:50.771
And by abundant life, Jesus is saying there is an overflowing quality of life that I want to give you.

05:51.392 --> 05:56.699
It's not just that Jesus wants to lengthen our life, but he wants to deepen our life.

05:56.999 --> 06:00.003
He wants to give our life meaning and purpose.

06:00.023 --> 06:03.347
That is what Jesus is referring to by this abundant life.

06:04.088 --> 06:06.791
But the contrast could not be more clear.

06:08.092 --> 06:09.394
Satan's goals,

06:09.666 --> 06:12.670
are to kill, to steal, and destroy.

06:12.710 --> 06:19.338
And for Jesus, he is always on the side of life, an abundant life.

06:20.519 --> 06:29.550
Satan's strategy is that through thoughts of hopelessness and worthlessness, that he can whisper to you, you'd be better off dead.

06:29.610 --> 06:31.913
That is a lie from the evil one.

06:32.834 --> 06:35.858
Those words are not from the voice of truth.

06:36.034 --> 06:39.738
They are the voice of a liar who has been a liar from the beginning.

06:40.759 --> 06:48.467
Some of you in this room are wrestling with thoughts that you've never told anyone else about.

06:49.468 --> 06:58.338
Some of you are in the soul crushing weight of shame or regret and you think there is no way out.

06:59.079 --> 07:02.322
Some of you are enduring so much emotional

07:02.594 --> 07:08.001
and mental pain right now that you just want and out.

07:08.922 --> 07:13.888
I want you to know there is a way out and his name is Jesus.

07:15.350 --> 07:16.451
That is the way out.

07:17.492 --> 07:19.835
He is the solution to your problem.

07:20.416 --> 07:23.119
It may not be an immediate solution.

07:23.159 --> 07:24.301
I want to say that.

07:24.521 --> 07:25.522
I want to be clear.

07:26.146 --> 07:31.234
I'm not promising you that tomorrow everything's going to be sunshine and roses and blue skies.

07:31.574 --> 07:32.616
That's not the truth.

07:33.537 --> 07:39.807
But what is the truth is that the alternative to life is always a mistake.

07:40.869 --> 07:47.840
So this morning, I want to spend the rest of my time separating the truth from lies about suicide.

07:48.320 --> 07:50.343
And I want to talk about five of them this morning.

07:50.964 --> 07:51.665
Here's the first.

07:53.008 --> 07:54.610
Suicide is not.

07:55.106 --> 07:56.608
the unpardonable sin.

07:56.668 --> 08:05.978
One of the things that you have heard said probably, and I get questions about sometimes, is suicide the unforgivable sin.

08:06.899 --> 08:08.421
Now, let me be very clear.

08:08.881 --> 08:15.228
The Bible says in the sixth commandment, in Exodus chapter 20 verse 17, you shall not commit murder.

08:16.149 --> 08:17.230
Murder is a sin.

08:17.290 --> 08:22.536
The word suicide comes from a Latin word.

08:22.736 --> 08:24.178
That means self,

08:24.578 --> 08:25.059
murder.

08:25.799 --> 08:33.809
So please understand that suicide is a sin, but it is not the unforgivable sin.

08:33.869 --> 08:40.698
The unforgivable sin according to Jesus is blasphemy against the Holy Spirit.

08:40.758 --> 08:43.541
That's what Jesus said in Matthew chapter 12 verse 31.

08:44.683 --> 08:49.288
Blasphemy of the Holy Spirit and suicide are not the same thing.

08:49.308 --> 08:50.770
They're not even in the same neighborhood.

08:51.394 --> 09:00.047
Now if I had time, we could plow into the ground of what is, blast me of the Holy Spirit, but simply understand this morning, it's not suicide.

09:01.409 --> 09:04.875
So where does this thought come from that it's the unforgivable sin?

09:05.836 --> 09:16.613
Well, there is a stream of thought in religious life that says that if you commit murder, then that's a really bad sin.

09:17.173 --> 09:20.178
So that one gets you alienated from God.

09:20.994 --> 09:24.099
Now, I don't usually call names, but just let me clarify it.

09:24.539 --> 09:28.986
In Roman Catholic theology, there are two types or categories of sin.

09:29.827 --> 09:31.049
One are called venial sins.

09:31.670 --> 09:32.731
Those are the little sins.

09:33.292 --> 09:36.397
Those are the sins you can be forgiven for by just confessing those.

09:37.258 --> 09:42.065
And those sins kind of irritate God, they kind of aggravate God, but they don't alienate you from God.

09:42.566 --> 09:43.868
But then there are mortal sins.

09:43.968 --> 09:46.171
I mean, the big ones and murder is one of those.

09:46.472 --> 09:47.954
And if you commit one of those,

09:48.514 --> 09:56.044
then you got to do some serious, confessing and penance and maybe even go to purgatory before you could go to heaven.

09:56.745 --> 10:00.971
I want you to understand all of those thoughts are found somewhere other than the Bible.

10:01.612 --> 10:04.856
Those are not even close to biblical theology.

10:05.297 --> 10:08.221
Categories of sin are untrue.

10:09.062 --> 10:12.887
Every sin alienates us from God, not just the big ones.

10:13.188 --> 10:16.072
There aren't any categories of sin with God.

10:16.693 --> 10:17.714
It's all bad.

10:18.050 --> 10:19.051
But here's the good news.

10:19.612 --> 10:25.479
On the cross, Jesus died for all my sins, past, present, and future.

10:25.799 --> 10:28.723
They are under the blood of the cross of Christ.

10:29.544 --> 10:32.007
And when it comes to suicide, I want you to know this.

10:32.508 --> 10:44.402
What one hopeless, confused person does in their darkest hour cannot undo what Jesus did on three dark hours on a cross one Friday.

10:45.730 --> 10:49.816
Real Christians get their sins forgiven at one time.

10:51.158 --> 10:55.544
All of our sins are atoned by the blood of Jesus Christ.

10:57.506 --> 11:02.694
There's a biblical example of someone who committed suicide and went to heaven.

11:04.095 --> 11:05.557
And his name is Samson.

11:06.399 --> 11:14.610
Samson is one of those guys that some of you may have heard of before, but what you know about him is he was a really strong guy, had really big muscles, and he had really long hair.

11:15.554 --> 11:19.318
Well, there's a lot more to Samson's story than that that I don't have time to tell.

11:19.378 --> 11:22.322
But Samson was uniquely gifted by God.

11:22.522 --> 11:24.604
He was given this great strength and great power.

11:24.944 --> 11:27.547
Samson's strength did not come from his hair.

11:28.028 --> 11:28.829
It came from God.

11:30.110 --> 11:33.194
And Samson was a ruler.

11:33.234 --> 11:34.755
He was a judge of Israel.

11:34.815 --> 11:37.138
So God used him in really incredible ways.

11:38.019 --> 11:40.722
But Samson made horrible decisions.

11:41.090 --> 11:43.513
He just made really bad decisions.

11:44.154 --> 11:49.021
And he was a guy who was ruled by his sexual appetites.

11:49.201 --> 11:53.927
And because of that, I mean, he just made really bad calls and bad decisions in his life.

11:54.949 --> 12:05.022
Such they were so bad that eventually God disciplined him and he allowed him to be captured by their enemies, the Philistines, had his eyes gouged out.

12:06.084 --> 12:07.666
Delilah did shave his hair.

12:08.226 --> 12:15.596
And that was the symbol of his strength, and so God spirit left him, and he left him powerless, and he was put in prison.

12:16.398 --> 12:19.262
But there in prison, he began to turn back to God.

12:20.063 --> 12:24.569
And in the last moment of his life, Samson prayed for his strength to return.

12:25.590 --> 12:30.818
In Judges, chapter 16, verse 30, Samson said, let me die with the Philistines.

12:31.319 --> 12:36.626
Then he pushed with all his might, and down came the temple on the rulers and all the people in it.

12:36.706 --> 12:39.569
Thus he killed many more when he died than when he lived.

12:40.530 --> 12:44.814
Samson knew that he was taking his own life.

12:46.036 --> 12:48.999
He knew that he was taking his own life.

12:49.920 --> 12:53.183
But there's something peculiar in the New Testament.

12:53.203 --> 12:56.386
In the New Testament, there's this chapter in Hebrews, chapter 11.

12:56.426 --> 12:57.848
You could read the whole thing if you wanted to.

12:58.689 --> 13:03.794
And it just details all these great people of faith, these people who

13:04.002 --> 13:06.565
who had been obedient to God and who had been righteous.

13:07.466 --> 13:15.214
Their stories told about Abraham and their stories told about Moses and their stories about all these heroes.

13:15.834 --> 13:21.460
And then the writer of Hebrews says this, and what more shall I say?

13:22.401 --> 13:31.090
For time will fail me if I tell a Gideon of Barak of, there he is, Samson.

13:31.778 --> 13:42.008
of Jeptha, of David and Samuel and the prophets who by faith conquered kingdoms, performed active righteousness, obtained promises, shut them out of lions.

13:42.829 --> 13:53.439
Samson, who took his own life, is mentioned in the same breath with David and Samuel and the heroes of the Old Testament faith.

13:54.300 --> 13:58.904
You see, suicide is a sin, but it is not the unforgivable sin.

13:59.845 --> 14:00.466
By the way,

14:01.058 --> 14:05.543
Never say to anyone who's had a family member friend commit suicide.

14:05.603 --> 14:07.425
Never say to them, it must have been God's will.

14:07.925 --> 14:08.566
No, it wasn't.

14:09.848 --> 14:13.532
Sin is never God's will.

14:13.552 --> 14:14.393
Ever.

14:14.413 --> 14:14.853
No sin.

14:16.014 --> 14:30.450
If a person is genuinely saved, their salvation rests on the finished work of Christ on the cross, not in their actions in their weakest moment.

14:31.330 --> 14:32.211
But I want you to hear me.

14:32.471 --> 14:35.434
Forgiveness does not equal permission.

14:36.115 --> 14:44.064
To take one's life is to reject God's sovereignty over life and to inflict devastating pain on those who are left behind.

14:45.425 --> 14:48.909
Number two, suicide is not a solution.

14:48.949 --> 14:51.892
It only creates more problems.

14:53.154 --> 15:00.882
Some people say, well, Bob, if a truly saved person commits suicide and they go to heaven, I mean, are you giving them a free pass?

15:01.250 --> 15:02.612
Shouldn't we keep that secret?

15:02.632 --> 15:05.375
Shouldn't we not like not telling that to try to prevent that?

15:06.797 --> 15:09.920
I believe truth is always the best answer.

15:10.981 --> 15:12.343
It's just always the best answer.

15:13.164 --> 15:13.965
So I want you to hear me.

15:15.306 --> 15:23.496
If you haven't trusted Jesus, if you haven't committed your life to Him, made Him your Lord and Savior, turn from your sin, received His free gift of salvation.

15:23.536 --> 15:28.562
If you've not done that and you commit suicide, the problems

15:28.674 --> 15:34.860
that are leading to that on this earth will seem tiny compared to the eternal suffering of hell.

15:36.442 --> 15:37.082
You need to hear that.

15:38.103 --> 15:56.562
If you have trusted Christ and decide to take your own life, the problems you are facing now will be small compared to the trail of pain and misery and chaos you will create

15:56.898 --> 15:59.481
in the lives of people who love you.

16:00.743 --> 16:08.773
And by the way, one of the lives the evil one tells people who are beginning to experience these thoughts is nobody cares about you.

16:09.174 --> 16:10.075
Nobody loves you.

16:10.295 --> 16:11.677
I want you to know something.

16:12.878 --> 16:14.541
Yes, they do.

16:15.642 --> 16:16.844
Your family loves you.

16:17.424 --> 16:18.946
You say, well, I don't know if I believe that.

16:19.367 --> 16:19.947
I won't tell you this.

16:20.228 --> 16:22.691
This church loves you and I can say that with authority.

16:23.372 --> 16:25.074
There are people who love you.

16:25.762 --> 16:27.384
That's one of Satan's biggest lies.

16:27.985 --> 16:34.374
But I want you to understand that suicide creates a massive problem.

16:34.694 --> 16:39.861
If you have a shred of love for those who love you, don't do this.

16:41.103 --> 16:44.288
In the Old Testament, there's another example of a man who committed suicide.

16:44.348 --> 16:45.389
His name was Saul.

16:46.471 --> 16:54.802
Saul was Israel's first king and he was uniquely blessed with God, of God, but he wasted God's blessings.

16:55.298 --> 16:58.942
and he was impetuous and made horrible decisions.

16:59.443 --> 17:05.029
Sometimes he went out and led Israel against their big enemy at the time, the Philistines.

17:05.910 --> 17:13.338
And in this occasion, because of Saul's sin and the sin of the nation, God allowed the Philistines to defeat them.

17:14.539 --> 17:18.324
And in the course of that battle, Samuel realized that he was defeated.

17:19.465 --> 17:20.466
The Bible says,

17:21.090 --> 17:30.200
in 1 Samuel 31 verse 3, the battle went heavily against Saul and the archers hit him and he was badly wounded by the archers.

17:31.201 --> 17:36.667
And then Saul said to his armor bearer, draw your sword and pierce me through with it.

17:36.767 --> 17:41.432
Otherwise these uncircumcised will come and pierce me through and make sport of me.

17:42.173 --> 17:46.037
But his armor bearer would not, for he was greatly afraid.

17:47.299 --> 17:50.482
So Saul took his sword and fell on it.

17:52.002 --> 17:53.684
He killed himself.

17:53.704 --> 17:59.873
When his armor bear saw that Saul was dead, he also fell in his sword and died with him.

18:02.216 --> 18:03.137
Two thoughts from that.

18:04.239 --> 18:12.290
The first is this, that Saul sent his army into chaos when he killed himself.

18:13.732 --> 18:21.362
And not only that, but his own family, when they heard news, they began to panic and there was chaos in his family.

18:22.594 --> 18:27.442
And what they would do is they tried to run from the advancing Philistines.

18:28.264 --> 18:31.770
And a nursemaid picked up one of Saul's infant sons.

18:31.810 --> 18:33.352
His name was Mephibosheth.

18:34.935 --> 18:41.606
And as she was running in the panic after Saul killed himself, she dropped Mephibosheth.

18:41.627 --> 18:46.034
And we don't know exactly what happened if there was an injury to his legs or hips

18:46.114 --> 18:52.064
or if there was a spinal cord injury, but Mephibosheth was paralyzed from the waist down for the rest of his life.

18:52.124 --> 18:54.548
He couldn't walk.

18:54.568 --> 18:59.176
You see, there was a consequence to Saul's action to his own son.

19:00.659 --> 19:11.858
And it may not be a physical consequence, but I'm going to tell you that a person who commits suicide leaves behind a trail of misery and pain that is undescribable.

19:13.378 --> 19:17.044
Family members of people who commit suicide live with devastating wounds.

19:17.725 --> 19:42.642
If you have a shred of love for your family, you need to know that your suicide would leave them scarred, doubting, hurting, and confused for the rest of their lives, not for a moment, not until the funeral's over, but forever, because Christmas will never be the same without you, ever.

19:44.258 --> 19:46.281
their days will never be the same.

19:47.162 --> 19:50.486
But also suicide can have a contagion effect.

19:50.506 --> 19:54.070
There is a social contagion effect of suicide.

19:55.893 --> 19:58.056
Saul's armor bear sees him commit suicide.

19:59.137 --> 20:04.964
He sees the situation as hopeless and he falls on his own sword and kills himself.

20:05.805 --> 20:09.490
High school counselors have told me that when there is a suicide

20:09.922 --> 20:18.775
in their school or even in a neighboring school, they are on the alert for that social contagion aspect of suicide.

20:19.977 --> 20:30.433
In 2017, Chester Bennington, the lead singer of the Rock Band Lincoln Park at the height of his success committed suicide.

20:32.095 --> 20:33.778
And it was tragic and horrible.

20:34.754 --> 20:39.882
But what made it all the more tragic was that he committed suicide in July of 2017.

20:40.483 --> 20:52.341
In May of 2017, his close friend, probably the person he called his best friend, Chris Cornell, the lead singer of Soundgarden, had also committed suicide.

20:53.503 --> 21:00.594
What made that just so stunning was that Bennington had written on social media after Cornell's death.

21:01.346 --> 21:05.131
I cannot imagine living in a world without you.

21:05.652 --> 21:10.959
He knew the pain of suicide and he did the same thing to his loved ones.

21:12.421 --> 21:18.430
Suicide is a permanent solution to a temporary problem.

21:19.511 --> 21:23.897
Most people who commit suicide do not want to die.

21:24.859 --> 21:27.663
They want the pain to end.

21:28.924 --> 21:30.066
That's what they desire.

21:31.202 --> 21:32.003
I want you to hear me.

21:33.185 --> 21:42.378
There is a faithful God who loves and he listens and he answers when we cry out to him.

21:43.320 --> 21:49.549
He will faithfully see you through whatever you are enduring.

21:49.589 --> 21:55.217
And I want to speak directly at this moment into some situations.

21:57.420 --> 21:58.802
One of the most

22:00.162 --> 22:15.018
dangerous moments, especially in the lives of young people and teenagers and young adults, is the loss of a relationship, a bad breakup.

22:16.460 --> 22:26.351
And those moments many times lead to suicide attempts and sometimes to their success.

22:27.913 --> 22:29.074
I want you to hear me.

22:30.274 --> 22:32.737
I know a broken heart is a real thing.

22:33.779 --> 22:40.929
I am not trivializing that in the least, but there is a plan beyond your broken heart.

22:43.332 --> 22:48.339
And if you could just see five years in the future, you would know that's true.

22:49.541 --> 22:58.834
Our former pastor's daughter, Julia Jefferson Sadler, has a podcast and she's spoken in school assemblies and she's talked about her own struggles.

22:59.298 --> 23:02.983
when she was a teenager and a part of this church, the pastor's daughter of this church.

23:03.043 --> 23:10.973
And she went to ride her high school and she had a tremendous emotional struggle and she could not see how life would ever get better.

23:12.335 --> 23:16.120
And now if you could see her, she has a ministry.

23:17.141 --> 23:18.283
She has a wonderful husband.

23:18.323 --> 23:21.407
She and Ryan Sadler, who also grew up here, got married.

23:22.268 --> 23:23.730
They have triplets.

23:24.194 --> 23:26.057
And they have a wonderful life.

23:26.157 --> 23:28.441
There was life beyond high school.

23:28.481 --> 23:31.947
There was life beyond her pain in those years.

23:32.247 --> 23:33.970
And I just want to plead with you.

23:34.271 --> 23:36.194
There is life beyond this.

23:37.917 --> 23:38.618
There is more.

23:40.081 --> 23:46.371
Number three, real Christians can be suicidal.

23:48.034 --> 23:50.578
Some people would say, well, if you're truly saved, you would never do that.

23:51.970 --> 23:55.575
Faithful people can get so depressed and downhearted that they want to die.

23:56.536 --> 23:57.618
Let me give you some names.

23:58.780 --> 24:06.390
Moses, Job, Elijah, Jeremiah, Jonah, and Paul.

24:08.173 --> 24:11.598
All of them got to a place where they wanted to die.

24:11.638 --> 24:13.801
Now, I'm not saying they all tried to commit suicide.

24:13.861 --> 24:14.802
That's not the case.

24:15.490 --> 24:18.835
but they all got to a place where they just wanted life to end.

24:18.875 --> 24:20.056
It became so painful.

24:20.417 --> 24:22.079
Listen to what the Apostle Paul said.

24:23.321 --> 24:37.401
For we do not want you to be unaware, brethren, of our affliction, which came to us in Asia, that we were burdened excessively beyond our strength so that we despaired even of life.

24:39.043 --> 24:41.266
Paul said, I just wanted to die.

24:42.370 --> 24:44.773
Moses said, God, would you please take me?

24:44.813 --> 24:46.975
Jeremiah said, I wish I'd never been born.

24:47.716 --> 24:49.438
Elijah said, it is enough.

24:49.478 --> 24:50.339
Take my life.

24:50.399 --> 24:53.743
And Jonah wished to die in Jonah, chapter four, verse three.

24:54.023 --> 25:00.170
They were so defeated, so despondent and so depressed that they wanted this life to end.

25:01.632 --> 25:10.802
You can be a true believer and experience the devastating effects of mental health issues and depression.

25:11.650 --> 25:25.573
The myth that a true follower of Jesus can't fall into darkness and experience suicidal thoughts is absolutely wrong and it's misleading.

25:26.835 --> 25:31.483
See, just because you are your loved one is saved, that is not an immunity.

25:32.625 --> 25:38.194
And I want you as parents to know that you need to be on the lookout for this with your kids.

25:38.978 --> 25:47.229
Even those who are saved and love Jesus, there are things that occur in their life and high school is hard and social media hadn't made it any better.

25:48.951 --> 25:51.655
Even worse now is AI.

25:51.695 --> 25:57.262
AI is not the devil, but it can be used by him.

25:57.563 --> 25:58.624
I am pretty convinced of that.

25:59.505 --> 26:05.874
A few weeks ago, Senator Josh Hawley brought six sets of parents before a United States Senate committee.

26:06.850 --> 26:29.018
All six of them had had children who had interacted with AI chatbots and the AI chatbots in their discussion back and forth with the AI had eventually convinced them to attempt suicide, to encourage self harm.

26:29.618 --> 26:35.666
And while investigations remain underway in those cases, it remind us

26:35.778 --> 26:46.849
of how vulnerable and how insidious our enemy who wants to steal and kill and destroy can be.

26:47.890 --> 26:50.232
And so parents, I want to encourage you.

26:50.293 --> 26:55.618
Number one, keep the lines of communication open even when it's uncomfortable.

26:55.638 --> 26:58.781
I know you don't want to talk about this, but somebody's got to.

27:01.203 --> 27:03.826
Second, watch for signs of depression.

27:04.226 --> 27:05.668
and suicidal ideation.

27:05.728 --> 27:06.609
What are some of those?

27:07.069 --> 27:12.975
Well, wild mood swings is certainly one of those things.

27:12.995 --> 27:14.617
Now look, I have a teenage daughter.

27:14.717 --> 27:21.705
I understand mood swings are a part of life, but there are sort of extremes that can go to.

27:21.725 --> 27:23.126
Let me give you another one.

27:24.467 --> 27:28.912
Giving away prized possessions to someone else.

27:29.353 --> 27:30.674
I want you to have this.

27:31.074 --> 27:34.618
And especially if you were to hear these words, I want you to have this to remember me.

27:37.301 --> 27:53.578
There are other signs that we could probably kind of research, but parents, I know you love your children, but we all sometimes get so busy and we want to believe that what's happening in our house, it just happens, but know that you need to keep an eye on them.

27:53.618 --> 27:57.202
Let them know that there's nothing ever so bad that suicide is the answer.

27:58.178 --> 28:00.881
It's a permanent solution to temporary problems.

28:00.981 --> 28:01.561
Let them know.

28:02.743 --> 28:04.284
Finally, seek professional help.

28:05.145 --> 28:08.468
If you had a doctor, if you had the flu, rather you'd go to a doctor.

28:09.289 --> 28:12.052
Why wouldn't we do that for a mental health issue?

28:12.232 --> 28:17.818
Number four, suicidal people are responsible for their decisions.

28:18.839 --> 28:25.065
Now, this is the uncomfortable one because what we would like to think is, well, they're not really responsible for their decisions.

28:25.565 --> 28:26.226
Yes, they are.

28:27.010 --> 28:33.679
Judas committed suicide, and Judas was an unbeliever, but Judas was responsible for his decision.

28:34.661 --> 28:42.672
Satan whispers the lie that what you do won't affect anybody else, and that is a lie.

28:43.313 --> 28:48.139
There's a story in the New Testament, the apostle Paul, he's in a jail in Philippi for preaching the gospel.

28:49.221 --> 28:55.890
And he and Silas are there, and about midnight the Bible says they're singing hymns and they're quoting scripture, they're just worshiping at midnight.

28:56.258 --> 29:00.845
When God sent an earthquake, it shook the jail and the prison doors flew open.

29:02.067 --> 29:06.373
When the prison doors flew open, what the jailer thought had happened was there'd been a jail break.

29:06.433 --> 29:07.956
I mean, these people got away.

29:09.057 --> 29:13.865
And in that world, if your prisoners got away, you were killed for it.

29:13.885 --> 29:16.228
That's the way they kept jailers from taking bribes.

29:18.191 --> 29:21.556
So the prison doors fly open and the jailer is about to kill himself.

29:22.538 --> 29:25.362
Listen to what the Apostle Paul,

29:25.570 --> 29:28.614
Luke records in the book of Acts that happened.

29:29.334 --> 29:36.202
When the jailer awoke and saw the prison doors opened, he drew his sword and was about to kill himself, supposing that the prisoners had escaped.

29:37.224 --> 29:42.249
But Paul cried out with a loud voice saying, do not harm yourself, for we are all here.

29:43.130 --> 29:46.094
And he called for lights and rushed in and trembling with fear.

29:46.134 --> 29:47.996
He fell down before Paul and Silas.

29:48.657 --> 29:53.042
And after he brought them out, he said, sirs, what must I do to be saved?

29:54.338 --> 29:58.163
They said, believe in the Lord Jesus Christ and you will be saved.

29:58.183 --> 29:59.224
You and your whole household.

30:00.426 --> 30:10.098
And they spoke the word of the Lord to him together with all those who were in his house and he took them that very hour of the night and he washed their wounds and immediately he was baptized.

30:10.939 --> 30:12.801
He and his whole household.

30:13.022 --> 30:16.166
That means his whole family got saved.

30:17.768 --> 30:22.674
A momentary, impetuous decision, a rash,

30:22.754 --> 30:32.264
decision that the Apostle Paul, if he had not interceded and intervened in, that Philippian jailer would be in hell.

30:34.807 --> 30:41.835
But as it was because he didn't, he heard the gospel and was saved and his entire family got saved.

30:42.556 --> 30:46.961
Your decisions do affect other people.

30:49.904 --> 30:51.986
Everything you do has an impact.

30:52.994 --> 31:01.106
And we can be sympathetic to the pain of mental illness and the problems that people have, but they are responsible for their decisions and there will be an accounting.

31:02.248 --> 31:14.806
Finally, number five, and I want to speak in this moment to those of you who have endured the pain of losing a loved one to suicide.

31:16.148 --> 31:22.738
Trusting God is the only way to cope with the suicide of a loved one.

31:25.730 --> 31:31.075
There is something about suicide that is so, so crushing that is so heavy.

31:32.236 --> 31:35.299
And I've seen people try to medicate themselves through it.

31:36.621 --> 31:40.965
I've seen people try to self-medicate themselves through it with alcohol.

31:41.445 --> 31:45.789
I need you to understand the end of your pain is not at the bottom of that bottle.

31:47.391 --> 31:54.578
It won't work because when you sober up, the pain will be there.

31:55.010 --> 31:56.031
and you'll have a hangover.

31:57.713 --> 31:58.875
You see, what happens is this.

32:00.617 --> 32:08.747
Satan, the liar, will come and he'll try to blame you and shame you and cripple you.

32:10.169 --> 32:21.484
He'll try to convince you that you were responsible, that if you just texted, if you just called, if you just answered their call, that somehow this would not have happened.

32:22.485 --> 32:23.346
I want you to know.

32:24.354 --> 32:29.120
The voice that says, you're responsible for this is not the voice of God.

32:30.002 --> 32:31.584
It's not the voice of truth.

32:32.805 --> 32:38.313
And it is not going to help for you to feel responsible for the actions of another.

32:39.875 --> 32:47.205
God will be faithful to you, to see you through the dark days of the suicide of a loved one.

32:48.306 --> 32:50.730
Rick Warren is a pastor in California.

32:50.790 --> 32:52.052
He's retired recently.

32:53.093 --> 32:53.874
He started

32:53.954 --> 32:57.678
Saddleback Church, and it became one of the largest churches in America.

32:58.679 --> 33:04.725
But in 2013, Rick and Kay, his wife, lost a son to suicide.

33:05.706 --> 33:14.875
He had struggled for many, many years, and one Saturday morning, they called, and he didn't answer, and they called again.

33:14.915 --> 33:18.498
He didn't answer, and something just told Rick, you got to go.

33:18.598 --> 33:22.322
And so Rick went over to his house and found his son.

33:23.778 --> 33:24.579
It was devastating.

33:24.859 --> 33:25.320
It's horrible.

33:26.401 --> 33:28.123
Words can't describe how terrible it was.

33:29.305 --> 33:52.754
But in an article, Rick wrote that what got them through, what continues to get them through, some 12 years later where the promises of God's Word, promises like Isaiah, chapter 43, verse 1, but now says the Lord, the Creator, O Jacob, He who formed you, O Israel, do not fear

33:53.666 --> 33:54.747
where I have redeemed you.

33:54.847 --> 33:56.148
I've called you by name.

33:56.429 --> 33:57.149
You are mine.

33:58.030 --> 34:03.315
When you pass through the waters, I will be with you and the rivers will not overflow you.

34:03.696 --> 34:08.800
When you walk through the fire, you will not be scorched nor will the flame burn you."

34:08.820 --> 34:17.409
And promises like Hebrews 13, 5, I will never desert you nor will I ever forsake you.

34:19.110 --> 34:22.994
If you have endured the horrible pain of the suicide of a loved one,

34:24.098 --> 34:33.656
God promises His faithful peace, power, and provision to see you through it.

34:33.676 --> 34:36.942
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

34:37.503 --> 34:46.520
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

34:46.540 --> 34:47.762
We'll see you next week.

